The paper discusses the coordination of markets through the use of prices, which is a central topic in game theory and economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses techniques from learning theory to analyze the performance of prices, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the computation of equilibrium prices, which falls under cs.EC (Economics and Computation). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to analyze the performance of prices, which could also place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
